==English==
===Etymology===
A corruption of an original [[gaelic]] word meaning noble. 

===Surname===

'''McQuarrie'''

The [[clan]] McQuarrie had holdings in the western [[highland]]s surrounding and centered in the Isle of Mull. 

===Trivia===
A notable MacQuarie was Lachland MacQuarie, the second colonial governer of Australia and a major general in the British army.


